# Styling Rules

## Bootstrap-First

Always use Bootstrap 5.3.2 utility classes before writing custom CSS. The entire UI is built on Bootstrap's grid, card, table, badge, button, and form components.

## Theme System — `--kb-*` Variables

This project uses a 44-theme system with light/dark mode support. All colors MUST come from CSS custom properties.

### Semantic Color Variables
- `--kb-primary`, `--kb-accent`, `--kb-info`, `--kb-success`, `--kb-warning`, `--kb-danger`
- `--kb-primary-fg`, `--kb-accent-fg`, etc. (foreground for solid backgrounds)
- `--kb-bg-body`, `--kb-bg-card`, `--kb-bg-subtle` (background hierarchy)
- `--kb-text-primary`, `--kb-text-secondary`, `--kb-text-muted` (text hierarchy)
- `--kb-border-subtle` (borders)

### Rules

1. **ZERO hardcoded colors** in HTML inline styles or JavaScript. Always use `var(--kb-*)`.
2. For muted backgrounds, use `*-muted` variants — never `bg-*-opacity-*`.
3. Solid background → pair with `text-*-fg`. Muted background → use `text-*`.
4. Chart.js colors: read via `getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--kb-primary')` at render time.
5. Charts must re-render when theme changes (destroy and recreate).

### HTML Attributes

```html
<html data-theme="default" data-mode="dark">
```

Theme switching via `window.KBTheme.setTheme(id)` and `window.KBTheme.setMode('light'|'dark')`. State persists in `localStorage` keys `kb-theme` and `kb-mode`.

### CSS Load Order (required)

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/theme-system.css">  <!-- Variable foundation -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/themes.css">          <!-- 44 theme definitions -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/main.css">             <!-- Component styles -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/layout.css">           <!-- Layout/responsive -->
```

### JS Load Order

```html
<script src="js/theme.js"></script>    <!-- Theme system (must be first) -->
<script src="js/charts.js"></script>   <!-- Chart renderers -->
<script src="js/app.js"></script>      <!-- Main application -->
```
